{"lemma":"أَعْجَمُو","slug":"أَعْجَمُو","root":"ع.ج.م","root_slug":"ع-ج-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ج-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28248"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speak or write unclearly or unintelligibly, to mumble, to lisp (sense 2)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to be incorrect, unclear or barbarous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to point letters or a text"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shut or lock (the door)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to boil strongly"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"having an impotence in speech"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"non-Arabic","examples":[{"text":"وَلَوْ نَزَّلْنَاهُ عَلَى بَعْضِ ٱلْأَعْجَمِينَ / فَقَرَأَهُ عَلَيْهِم مَا كَانُوا بِهِ مُؤْمِنِينَ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ع ج م (ʕ j m)."},"ipa":["/ʔaʕ.d͡ʒa.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28248","headword_ar":"اَعْجَمُ","root":"Ejm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having an impotence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impediment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a difficulty, in speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utterance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) though he may be clear, perspicuous, distinct, chaste, or correct, in speaking a foreign language; (S;) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barbarous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitious therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not clear, perspicuous, distinct, chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in speaking Arabic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, * K, *) though he may be an Arab; (S, Mgh, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamiY~N","text_ar":"اَعْجَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, (Mgh, Msb, K,) and therefore, if applied to an Arab, it does not imply reproach; (Msb; [but it is said in the Mgh that this demands consideration;]) or this latter epithet is applied to a tongue, or speech, and to a book, or writing, but not to a man unless it be syn. with the former epithet: (S:) the fem. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb:) and the dual masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamaAni","text_ar":"اَعْجَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaAwaAni","text_ar":"عَجْمَاوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Har p. 226;) and the pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamuwna","text_ar":"اَعْجَمُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAjimu","text_ar":"اَعَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EujomaAnN","text_ar":"عُجْمَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamiY~N","text_ar":"اَعْجَمِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamiy~uwna","text_ar":"اَعْجَمِيُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajamN","text_ar":"عَجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence, in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dumb; speechless; destitute of the faculty of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unable to speak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaEojimN","text_ar":"مُسْتَعْجِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) fem. of the former as above. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence, (S,) by predominance of its application, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahiymapN","text_ar":"بَهِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaEojimN","text_ar":"مُسْتَعْجِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the fem. of this]: (TA:) pl. of the former in this sense, as a subst.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaAwaAtN","text_ar":"عَجْمَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p. 13:) [and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied [also] as an epithet to a beast, or brute, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bhymp","text_ar":"بهيمة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) for the like reason. (Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juroHu AlEajomaA='i jubaArN","text_ar":"جُرْحُ العَجْمَا=ءِ جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbr","text_ar":"جبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Mgh.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN A^aEojamu","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ اَعْجَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brays in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqo$iqap","text_ar":"شِقْشِقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faucial bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which there is no perforation, so that the sound does not issue from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and they approve of the sending such among the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awol","text_ar":"شَوْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or she-camels that have passed seven or eight months since the period of their bringing forth] because he usually begets females. (TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer of the daytime"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the reciting [of the Kur-án] therein is inaudible; (S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer of noon"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of afternoon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and these two together are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEajomaAwaAni","text_ar":"العَجْمَاوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 226.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawojN A^aEojamu","text_ar":"مَوْجٌ اَعْجَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Waves that do not sprinkle their water, and of which no sound is heard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajomaA='u","text_ar":"عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolapN EajomaA='u","text_ar":"رَمْلَةٌ عَجْمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tract of sand in which are no trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","Mgh","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}